-- MOVES- Flood Re, London Stock Exchange Group, ANZ, Bain Capital
-- 
-- Wed Jul 16, 2014 10:41AM EDT
-- None



July 16 (Reuters) - The following financial services industry appointments were announced on Wednesday. To inform us of other job changes, email moves@thomsonreuters.com.

FLOOD RE The Association of British Insurers (ABI) said Brendan McCafferty was appointed chief executive of Flood Re, the UK government-backed flood insurance scheme. [ID:nL4N0PR4FM]  PRIVATE ADVISORS LLC The asset management company said it had hired two senior investment professionals. Zac McCarroll and Richard Wiltshire join as managing directors. [ID:nL4N0PR4DF]  SMITH & WILLIAMSON INVESTMENT MANAGEMENT LLP  The UK-based investment management company said it added John Anderson to its fixed income team as partner. [ID:nL4N0PR4BS]  LONDON STOCK EXCHANGE GROUP <LSE.L>  The chairman of London Stock Exchange Group (LSE) <LSE.L> is to step down by the end of 2015 after more than a decade in the role, he told shareholders at the company's annual general meeting on Wednesday. [ID:nL6N0PR3Q8]  SNIPER CAPITAL LTD  The investment management company appointed Robin Duxfield as chief operating officer. [ID:nL4N0PR3OA]  HARCOURT INVESTMENT CONSULTING AG  The Zurich-based privately owned investment manager named Michel Salden as senior portfolio manager of the Vontobel Fund - Belvista Commodity. [ID:nL4N0PR3LE]  AMUNDI The Paris-based asset manager said it appointed Yasunori Iwanaga chief investment officer of Amundi Japan. [ID:nL4N0PR3GJ]  ACTIS CAPITAL LLP The London-based private equity firm said it appointed Shami Nissan as a director in the company's responsible investment team. [ID:nL4N0PR3B6]  MAYBANK KIM ENG SECURITIES <MBKET.BK>  The brokerage appointed Harmeet Singh Bedi chief executive of Singapore. [ID:nL4N0PR36Z]  AUSTRALIA AND NEW ZEALAND BANKING GROUP LTD <ANZ.AX>  The bank said it appointed Mary MacLeod chief financial officer for international and institutional banking. [ID:nL4N0PR309]  BAIN CAPITAL VENTURES Enrique Salem, the former chief executive of Symantec Corp <SYMC.O>, is joining Bain Capital Ventures, the venture capital arm of the private equity firm Bain Capital. Salem will focus on investing in software companies, the firm said in a statement. [ID:nL2N0PQ2JP]  PSIGMA INCOME FUND